1)	Launch a Ubuntu EC2 instance and login inside it.

2)	Update the system packages 
    # sudo apt-get update

3) Install the apache2 package
    # sudo apt install apache2 -y

4) Start and enable the apache service
   # sudo systemctl start apache2 && systemctl enable apache2

5) Remove the default test page index.html under /var/www/html, create a new test page index.html and write something inside it
   # vim index.html
     Hi! We are testing this webpage

6) Get the public IP and paste on the browser, it should display the text (You need to add the HTTP protocol in security groups for this to work) 
